<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Sometimes people argue that insider trading is=
 good. We want market prices to be accurate, to reflect all available infor=
mation; that way the best projects will get financed and people will be abl=
e to buy and sell assets at=C2=A0prices that reflect their real values. Let=
ting, say, corporate executives buy their stocks when they know good news i=
s coming, or sell them when they know bad news is coming, makes prices more=
 accurate. So we should encourage it. That is the theory. You don=E2=80=99t=
 hear it a lot these days about the stock market, but you do hear it someti=
mes. Here=E2=80=99s a recent=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbus=
iness.com/click/34337106.258392/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnByLm9yZy8yMDI0LzAyLzA3LzE=
xOTc5NTY3Njkvb3JnYW4tZG9uYXRpb24td29ya3BsYWNlLXJldmVuZ2UtaW5zaWRlci10cmFkaW=
5n/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb03a594c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"i=
temscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none =
!important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-=
bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Planet Money episode</a>=C2=
=A0halfheartedly making the case.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><em>Outside=C2=A0</em>of the stock market, tho=
ugh, this idea is more popular. =E2=80=9CIn boxing, it=E2=80=99s generally =
accepted =E2=80=94 if not condoned =E2=80=94 that [managers] sometimes bet =
on their fighters to win,=E2=80=9D the Wall Street Journal=C2=A0<a href=3D"=
https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34337106.258392/aHR0cHM6Ly93d=
3cud3NqLmNvbS9zcG9ydHMvYm94aW5nLXRlbGxlei1uYXZhcnJvLWpha2UtcGF1bC11bmRlcmNh=
